summary: I’ll never forgive marvel for getting my hopes up & giving us one last glimpse of bearded!steve in the cap marvel end credits...
body: I’ll never forgive marvel for getting my hopes up & giving us one last glimpse of bearded!steve in the cap marvel end credits scene and then being like SIKE………………:not only that but the tonal shift was almost abrasive. in the cap marvel end scene that Felt like steve rogers. the wound was open and he was hurt and soft and he had just lost his best friends and teammates and the world was falling apart and there was nothing he could do except mourn and watch the death toll rise. endgame steve felt wooden and unfamiliar

summary: I realize why I don’t like the Captain Marvel movie very much. I don’t like it because I really wanted to see Carol Danvers...
body: I realize why I don’t like the Captain Marvel movie very much. I don’t like it because I really wanted to see Carol Danvers before she became a superhero - I wanted to see her, completely hero, fighting sexism in the military, forming bonds with the few other women in the force, having fun and living life. But all we see from that is a few flashbacks and that really disappointed me. The whole “I am just a human and that’s enough” emotional climax would have made 100x more sense if we actually got to see her human side, not just a few short flashbacks here and there
